We examined richness and diversity of organic and conventional rotations and land-use by using Shannon’s diversity and equitability indices. Shannon’s diversity index (H, Eq. 1) helped to assess the relative abundance of crop categories, providing an indication about species diversity, while the Equitability index (EH, Eq. 2) helped to assess whether the different crop categories have an even share in both rotations and land-use. The two indices were calculated as follows:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
